{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":457,"text":"Throughout the history of computers"},{"time":3581,"text":"we've been striving\nto shorten the gap between us"},{"time":6828,"text":"and digital information,"},{"time":8422,"text":"the gap between our physical world"},{"time":10256,"text":"and the world in the screen"},{"time":12054,"text":"where our imagination can go wild."},{"time":14896,"text":"And this gap has become shorter,"},{"time":18823,"text":"shorter, and even shorter,"},{"time":21588,"text":"and now this gap is shortened down"},{"time":23232,"text":"to less than a millimeter,"},{"time":24542,"text":"the thickness of a touch-screen glass,"},{"time":26420,"text":"and the power of computing"},{"time":27870,"text":"has become accessible to everyone."},{"time":32773,"text":"But I wondered, what if there\ncould be no boundary at all?"},{"time":37812,"text":"I started to imagine\nwhat this would look like."},{"time":41556,"text":"First, I created this tool"},{"time":44007,"text":"which penetrates into the digital space,"},{"time":46516,"text":"so when you press it hard on the screen,"},{"time":48607,"text":"it transfers its physical\nbody into pixels."},{"time":51940,"text":"Designers can materialize their ideas"},{"time":54052,"text":"directly in 3D,"},{"time":55748,"text":"and surgeons can practice\non virtual organs"},{"time":58300,"text":"underneath the screen."},{"time":60524,"text":"So with this tool, this\nboundary has been broken."},{"time":65421,"text":"But our two hands still\nremain outside the screen."},{"time":68388,"text":"How can you reach inside and interact"},{"time":70872,"text":"with the digital information"},{"time":72299,"text":"using the full dexterity of our hands?"},{"time":75303,"text":"At Microsoft Applied Sciences,"},{"time":77605,"text":"along with my mentor Cati Boulanger,"},{"time":79521,"text":"I redesigned the computer"},{"time":80792,"text":"and turned a little space\nabove the keyboard"},{"time":83673,"text":"into a digital workspace."},{"time":86038,"text":"By combining a transparent\ndisplay and depth cameras"},{"time":88539,"text":"for sensing your fingers and face,"},{"time":90189,"text":"now you can lift up your hands\nfrom the keyboard"},{"time":92499,"text":"and reach inside this 3D space"},{"time":95337,"text":"and grab pixels with your bare hands."},{"time":97837,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":100808,"text":"Because windows and files have\na position in the real space,"},{"time":105014,"text":"selecting them is as easy\nas grabbing a book off your shelf."},{"time":108373,"text":"Then you can flip through this book"},{"time":110526,"text":"while highlighting the lines, words"},{"time":112243,"text":"on the virtual touch pad\nbelow each floating window."},{"time":114807,"text":"Architects can stretch\nor rotate the models"},{"time":117342,"text":"with their two hands directly."},{"time":119767,"text":"So in these examples,"},{"time":121387,"text":"we are reaching into the digital world."},{"time":124124,"text":"But how about reversing its role"},{"time":126470,"text":"and having the digital\ninformation reach us instead?"},{"time":131289,"text":"I'm sure many of us\nhave had the experience"},{"time":133361,"text":"of buying and returning items online."},{"time":135468,"text":"But now you don't have to worry about it."},{"time":137445,"text":"What I got here is an online\naugmented fitting room."},{"time":142083,"text":"This is a view that you get from"},{"time":143985,"text":"head-mounted or see-through display"},{"time":145729,"text":"when the system understands\nthe geometry of your body."},{"time":150876,"text":"Taking this idea further,\nI started to think,"},{"time":154427,"text":"instead of just seeing\nthese pixels in our space,"},{"time":157796,"text":"how can we make it physical"},{"time":159318,"text":"so that we can touch and feel it?"},{"time":163580,"text":"What would such a future look like?"},{"time":166629,"text":"At MIT Media Lab,\nalong with my advisor Hiroshi Ishii"},{"time":170287,"text":"and my collaborator Rehmi Post,"},{"time":172310,"text":"we created this one physical pixel."},{"time":175954,"text":"Well, in this case, this spherical magnet"},{"time":178578,"text":"acts like a 3D pixel in our space,"},{"time":180930,"text":"which means that both computers and people"},{"time":183834,"text":"can move this object to anywhere"},{"time":185732,"text":"within this little 3D space."},{"time":187701,"text":"What we did was essentially\ncanceling gravity"},{"time":191193,"text":"and controlling the movement by combining"},{"time":193332,"text":"magnetic levitation\nand mechanical actuation"},{"time":196156,"text":"and sensing technologies."},{"time":198633,"text":"And by digitally programming the object,"},{"time":201138,"text":"we are liberating\nthe object from constraints"},{"time":203915,"text":"of time and space, which means that now,"},{"time":207350,"text":"human motions can be\nrecorded and played back"},{"time":211246,"text":"and left permanently\nin the physical world."},{"time":214865,"text":"So choreography can be taught\nphysically over distance"},{"time":217898,"text":"and Michael Jordan's famous\nshooting can be replicated"},{"time":220494,"text":"over and over as a physical reality."},{"time":223972,"text":"Students can use this as a tool"},{"time":226152,"text":"to learn about the complex concepts"},{"time":228094,"text":"such as planetary motion, physics,"},{"time":232178,"text":"and unlike computer screens or textbooks,"},{"time":234997,"text":"this is a real, tangible experience"},{"time":237479,"text":"that you can touch and feel,\nand it's very powerful."},{"time":241137,"text":"And what's more exciting"},{"time":243119,"text":"than just turning what's currently\nin the computer physical"},{"time":246467,"text":"is to start imagining\nhow programming the world"},{"time":249656,"text":"will alter even our daily\nphysical activities."},{"time":255460,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":257942,"text":"As you can see, the digital information"},{"time":260699,"text":"will not just show us something"},{"time":262217,"text":"but it will start directly acting upon us"},{"time":264327,"text":"as a part of our physical surroundings"},{"time":266626,"text":"without disconnecting\nourselves from our world."},{"time":270824,"text":"Today, we started by talking\nabout the boundary,"},{"time":275170,"text":"but if we remove this boundary,"},{"time":277850,"text":"the only boundary left is our imagination."},{"time":281738,"text":"Thank you."},{"time":282986,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}